Subject: [PATCH AP-08] vmnet: replace do_gettimeofday with ktime_get_real_ts64 (kernel >= 5.0)

do_gettimeofday() was removed in Linux 5.0. vmnet's bridge.c calls it in
debug-logging code paths (inside #if LOGLEVEL >= 4 blocks) to timestamp
bridge events.

The fix wraps all three affected sites with LINUX_VERSION_CODE guards:
- The static `struct timeval vnetTime` variable is conditionalized to use
  `struct timespec64` on kernel >= 5.0
- The two `do_gettimeofday()` call sites are replaced with `ktime_get_real_ts64()`
  on kernel >= 5.0

Note: These code paths are only active when LOGLEVEL >= 4, which is not set
in normal builds. However, the fix ensures the code compiles cleanly even
if someone enables debug logging.

Source note: In VMware Workstation Pro 25H2u1, the static vnetTime declaration
is wrapped inside an existing '#if LOGLEVEL >= 4 ... #endif' block (lines ~73-75
of vmnet-only/bridge.c). The patch therefore replaces the entire LOGLEVEL guard
block with a nested LINUX_VERSION_CODE guard inside it, rather than replacing
just the bare declaration. For the older 6.16.x community overlay the declaration
is not wrapped and the replacement targets the bare line directly.

Applied by: _autopatch_bridge_gettimeofday() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  source contains do_gettimeofday AND not already guarded AND kernel >= 5.0

---
 vmnet-only/bridge.c | 28 +++++++++++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/vmnet-only/bridge.c b/vmnet-only/bridge.c
--- a/vmnet-only/bridge.c
+++ b/vmnet-only/bridge.c
@@ -71,8 +71,14 @@ static int         vnetBridgeFakeEthEncap = 0;
 #endif
 
-#if LOGLEVEL >= 4
-static struct timeval vnetTime;
-#endif
+#if LOGLEVEL >= 4
+#  if LINUX_VERSION_CODE < KERNEL_VERSION(5, 0, 0)
+static struct timeval vnetTime;
+#  else
+static struct timespec64 vnetTime;
+#  endif
+#endif
 
@@ -695,7 +701,11 @@ VNetBridgeReceiveFromVNet(VNetJack *this, struct sk_buff *skb)
 #      if LOGLEVEL >= 4
-      do_gettimeofday(&vnetTime);
+      /* [autopatch] */\
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE < KERNEL_VERSION(5, 0, 0)
+         do_gettimeofday(&vnetTime)
+#else
+         ktime_get_real_ts64(&vnetTime)
+#endif
 #      endif
 
@@ -1491,8 +1506,12 @@ VNetBridgeReceiveFromDev(VNetJack *this, struct sk_buff *skb)
 #  if LOGLEVEL >= 4
    {
-      struct timeval now;
-      do_gettimeofday(&now);
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE < KERNEL_VERSION(5, 0, 0)
+      struct timeval now;
+      do_gettimeofday(&now);
+#else
+      struct timespec64 now;
+      ktime_get_real_ts64(&now);
+#endif
